Author: haha#6652
Content: If I 51% attack bitcoin can I censor transactions?

Author: Regnar#6164
Content: if you control 51% of hashpower you decide what is in a block you mine, so they could be empty. But you would have to maintain 51% control forever to keep censoring. Their transactions are sitting in the mempool and if you aren't beating all the other miners to another block then they will mine them.

Author: Regnar#6164
Content: But that's very expensive and the resources to attack Bitcoin aren't really available (renting hashpower, or buying enough new miners). So people opt to gain 51% of smaller chains that are Nicehashable, they don't do this to censor transactions though, usually they do it to double spend deposits to an exchange
